## ğŸš€ Installation (The One-Line Method)
Follow these steps to "Behead" your server and bring the Zombie online.

1. **Download and Prepare**: Paste this into your terminal to 
    download the master installer and give it permission to run:
   curl -O https://raw.githubusercontent.com/markvx1irondestroyer-hub/-MERCURY-THE-FULL-HEADLESS-ZOMBIE-EDITION-v1.2-/main/install-headless.sh && chmod +x install-headless.sh

2. **Execute the Beheading**: Run the script to install drivers and disable the GUI:
   ./install-headless.sh

3. **Reboot & Wake**: After the system reboots headless, wake the stack:
   m up
### While the "One-Line Method" handles the heavy lifting of installing drivers 
And deploying containers, your server is not truly functional yet. 
You must complete several manual configuration steps to link these apps together and secure your data.
If you are having trouble setting the services up or need to transfer files. use m gui-on to to temporarily 
Return to Desktop the m gui-off when finished 
âœ… FINAL MISSION: THE "YOU'RE NOT DONE" CHECKLIST
The script finished, but the Zombie needs a soul. Complete these steps in order:
1. Secure the Command Center (Portainer)
 * Action: Open http://your-ip:9443 on your phone browser.
 * Task: Create your admin password immediately to prevent unauthorized access to your containers.
2. Sync the "Arr" Empire (Prowlarr)
 * Action: Go to http://your-ip:9696.
 * Task:
   * Add your indexers (torrent sites/trackers).
   * Navigate to Settings > Apps and add Sonarr and Radarr.
   * Copy the API Keys from the "General" settings of Sonarr/Radarr and paste them into Prowlarr to link them.
3. Claim Your Library (Jellyfin & Jellyseerr)
 * Action: Open Jellyfin (http://your-ip:8096) first to create your media libraries (Movies/TV).
 * Action: Open Jellyseerr (http://your-ip:5055).
 * Task: Use your Jellyfin login to sign in, then follow the setup wizard to link your Radarr and Sonarr instances using their API keys.
4. Lock the Vault (Hard Drive)
 * Action: If you haven't already, run ./mount-vault.sh.
 * Task: Verify your external drive is mounted to /media/linux/Expansion so Jellyfin can actually see your movies.
5. Remote Control: TTYD 
 * Go to: 7681 and setup TTYD Web UI for Terminal Control 
6. Remote Access: Tailscale (https://login.tailscale.com/admin/machines)
 * Authenticate and Connect â€‹Log In: If you haven't already, open your browser and sign in.
 * Make to setup your server PC as an Exit Node to access your web UIs off your local Network 
 * â€‹The "Magic" IP: Every device gets a unique, stable 100.x.y.z IP address. 
 * This stays the same regardless of what network youâ€™re on.
 * â€‹Check the Console: Visit your Tailscale Admin Console to see all your connected devices in one list.
 * â€‹tailscale status: See what else is on your network.
 * â€‹tailscale ip -4: Quickly grab your Tailscale IPv4 address.
 * â€‹tailscale ping <device-name>: Test the connection and see if it's a direct "peer-to-peer" link.
